  <prompt>Modify `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs:21-30` `UseAzureMonitor()` guard to THROW `InvalidOperationException` in non-Development environments when `APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_CONNECTION_STRING` is missing or empty. Today silently skips. Throw must mirror the existing `CacheModule` 4-branch fail-fast pattern (R1 FR-03). Development env continues to start with null conn string.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer with ASP.NET Core minimal API + Azure Monitor exporter familiarity. Apply `task-execute` skill at FULL rigor.</role>
  <goal>BFF startup in Production env with missing APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_CONNECTION_STRING throws `InvalidOperationException` with actionable message. Development env continues to start with null conn string. Unit test added covering both branches.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>Spec FR-06: today the guard silently skips `UseAzureMonitor()` if the conn string is missing. In Production this is invisible failure — App Insights pipeline dead, no telemetry, no one notices until someone queries customMetrics and sees nothing. Fail-fast mirrors `CacheModule` 4-branch pattern from R1 FR-03 (R1 task 003).</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs (MODIFY — lines ~21-30 UseAzureMonitor block)</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Cache/CacheModule.cs (REFERENCE — 4-branch fail-fast pattern)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Startup/ (target dir for new unit test)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-06 — throw in non-Development envs when APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_CONNECTION_STRING is missing/empty.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Development env preserved: null conn string → continue startup.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-009 R1 amendment">Fail-fast pattern (no silent in-memory fallback) generalized to other telemetry/startup concerns.</constraint>
